Description: Part of a conical jar-sealing: of pale grey clay with an impressed inscription giving the repeated name of Den. The impression occurs three times on the seal but only one is substantially complete. The surface of the clay is well preserved.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl.XXIV, 44; P. Kaplony, 'Die Inschriften der Ägyptischen Frühzeit III (Wiesbaden, 1964), pl.55, abb.202D; see also vol. II, 1119.
